qtsumm_121,Yi-1.5-34B,121,"In the years from 1996 to 2017, how did the leadership changes from Alfred Sant to Joseph Muscat affect the overall performance of the Labour Party in the general elections?","Table Title: Labour Party (Malta) - General elections

,From 1996 to 2017, Labour Party performance in general elections get better with change in leader from Alfred Sant to Joseph Muscat. During time of Sant, Labour Party have not stable results, winning majority in 1996 but then lose majority in elections of 1998 and 2003. Even though there is small improvement in number of votes in 2003, party still in opposition when Sant is leader.  When Joseph Muscat become party leader in 2013, Labour Party get majority in general elections, get 54.8% of votes and win 39 from 69 seats. This good thing continue in next election in 2017, the Labour Party vote share become 55.0% and keep majority in government with 37 from 67 seats.","Between 1996 and 2017, the Labour Party experienced two leadership changes: Alfred Sant led the party to win the majority in two elections out of five, while Joseph Muscat's leadership improved the party's performance, winning the majority in all four elections from 2013 to 2017, with 39, 37, 34, and 34 seats respectively.","From 1996 to 2017, the Labour Party was led by Alfred Sant and Joseph Muscat. Under Alfred Sant's leadership, the party won the majority in the 1996 election with 50.7% of the votes and 35 out of 69 seats. However, in the subsequent elections of 1998, 2003, and 2008, the party did not secure a majority, obtaining 47.0%, 47.5%, and 48.8% of the votes, and 30, 30, and 34 seats respectively. Joseph Muscat became the leader and led the party to victory in the 2013 and 2017 elections, securing a majority with 54.8% and 55.0% of the votes, and winning 39 out of 69 seats in 2013 and 37 out of 67 seats in 2017. This indicates an improvement in the party's performance under Muscat's leadership, as they consistently won the majority in both elections during his tenure.","Between 1996 and 2017, the Labour Party experienced a leadership change from Alfred Sant to Joseph Muscat. Under Alfred Sant's leadership, the party won the majority in the 1996 election with 35 seats but did not win a majority in the subsequent elections of 1998, 2003, and 2008. Joseph Muscat led the party to win the majority in both the 2013 and 2017 elections, securing 39 seats in 2013 and 37 seats in 2017."
